cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CE, cs.DB 

The paper presents a new genetic programming system that uses geometric semantic operators to solve a real-life application in the field of pharmacokinetic. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Additionally, the paper deals with optimization and prediction tasks, which could also fit into cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science) and cs.DB (Databases).
